									</ul>
										<p class="wp-block-observer-listicle__copy">The film “Sound of Freedom” became a massive hit but was beset by unfounded conspiracy theories and controversies. <a href="https://observer.com/company/rcpmk/" title="R&amp;CPMK" class="company-link">R&amp;CPMK</a> was brought in to reshape the narrative and amplify the movie's real meaning. It was just the tip of a very large iceberg for R&amp;CPMK, which continues to blend brands and boldface names in ways few firms match. Along with clients including Amazon Prime Video, Samsung, Bacardi and Mastercard, the 250-person agency added names like Lizzo, global star Fan Bingbing, and TV’s Mark Consuelos to a regal roster that numbers Arnold Schwarzenegger, Elton John, Machine Gun Kelly, Brie Larson; the firm has also supported clients Bruce Willis and Jeremy Renner through much-reported-on challenges.</p>
			
