							<ul class="wp-block-observer-listicle__subtitle-list">
											<li class="wp-block-observer-listicle__subtitle-element">
							<strong><a href="https://observer.com/person/michael-tavani/" title="Michael Tavani" class="company-link">Michael Tavani</a></strong>						</li>
									</ul>
										<p class="wp-block-observer-listicle__copy">Even before its majority investment from <a href="https://observer.com/company/berlin-rosen/" title="Berlin Rosen" class="company-link">Berlin Rosen</a> in May 2023, this real estate/hospitality PR machine was on track for its biggest year since its founding in 2010. Among <a href="https://observer.com/company/m18/" title="M18" class="company-link">M18</a>'s clients and projects in more than 40 cities worldwide: Miami Freedom Park, the gargantuan new stadium/mixed-use project for Lionel Messi’s Inter Miami; ten hospitality projects across Texas, with even more on tap for 2024; and some of Atlanta’s biggest development initiatives, including Hawks owner Tony Ressler’s $5 billion Centennial Yards downtown megadevelopment. New clients include Chicago investment behemoths Sterling Bay, Canadian developer Great Gulf, and Manhattan’s Bjarke Ingels-designed One High Line towers.  And longtime clients keep funneling new projects M18’s way, including Extell, LeFrak, Related, Rockefeller Group, and Mast Capital.</p>
			
